This paper discusses defenses for a peer-to-peer digital preservation system, which involves distributed computing and network security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses attacks and defenses, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves data structures and algorithms for efficient resource management, which could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses network infrastructure and communication protocols, which could be categorized under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper involves system design and implementation, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Systems and Control).
